{"word":"ὄψ","slug":"ὄψ","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὄψ</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>only used in obl. cases of sg. <el>ὀπός, ὀπί, ὄπα</el>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>εἰπεῖν</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a voice</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>; of flutes, <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>a word</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}